  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate the rate of wound healing using sharp debridement
      using curette and to compare between such intensive treatment at hospital and treatment in
      primary care. A correlation between change in wound size and pro-inflammatory cytokines will
      also be made.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Subjects with chronic venous leg ulcers are treated 3 times a week in the hospital for 6
      weeks with weekly sharp debridement. Wound size, pro-inflammatory cytokines, smears and photo
      are made weekly. The treatment countinue thereafter in primary care 3 times a week in 12
      weeks. Wound size, pro-inflammatory cytokines, smears and photo are made every 14 day at the
      hospital.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
